  "prompt": "How do I close a chase savings account online?",
  "response": "To close a Chase savings account online, follow these steps:\n\n1. Log in to your Chase online banking account\n\n2. Navigate to the account you want to close\n\n3. If available, look for an option like \"Close Account\" or \"Request Account Closure\"\n\n4. If you can't find an online option, you'll need to:\n- Call Chase customer service at 1-800-935-9935\n- Visit a local Chase branch in person\n- Send a secure message through online banking\n\nImportant notes:\n- Transfer or withdraw all remaining funds before closing\n- Ensure all pending transactions are complete\n- Have alternative account information ready if transferring funds\n- Check for any early account closure fees\n\nIf you're having trouble or prefer personal assistance, it's recommended to call Chase directly for guidance specific to your account.",
